# Go AI Backend – apps/backend

Stateless Gin service: Supabase JWT in → Groq inference → structured extraction out. No database access, ever — mobile persists results itself.

## Layout

```
cmd/server/         main: config, routes, graceful shutdown
internal/config/    env loading (SUPABASE_URL, GROQ_API_KEY)
internal/auth/      JWKS ES256 verification (lestrrat-go/jwx) + per-user rate limit
internal/groq/      HTTP client, model constants, JSON-mode helpers
internal/extract/   text/image/notification extraction + wallet ladder + prompts
internal/chat/      finance Q&A from pre-aggregated snapshot
```

## Conventions

- Handlers bind with `ShouldBindJSON`; invalid body → `400 {"error": "...", "details": ...}`. All error responses use `{ error, details? }`.
- Extraction endpoints return HTTP 200 with a discriminated `Result` (`ok | skipped | unavailable`) — model/provider failures become `unavailable`, NOT 5xx, because the mobile queue treats `unavailable` as retryable.
- Wire structs in `internal/extract/types.go` use camelCase JSON and must mirror `apps/mobile/lib/ai/client/types.ts`. LLM-facing schemas are snake_case (see prompts) and mapped explicitly.
- Model choice via constants in `internal/groq/models.go` — fast model for live flows, quality model for fallback/insights, vision model for images. Don't inline model IDs elsewhere.
- LLM calls: `groq.CompleteJSON` (JSON mode + fence-stripping + unmarshal). Live flows keep `MaxRetryWait` ≤ 5s; background flows may wait longer on 429.
- Wallet resolution: model picks `wallet_id` from `AVAILABLE_WALLETS` in the prompt; backend validates ids against the client list, then deterministic hint fallback, `nil` when unsure (user picks in review modal). Never invent wallet IDs.
- Tests colocated `*_test.go`; fake Groq with `httptest`; auth tests generate a local ES256 JWK. Run `go test ./...` and `go vet ./...` before finishing.
